-- Mexico Stocks: Aeromexico, Penoles, Sports World Shares Advance
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-01-09T21:40:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/mexico-stocks-aeromexico-sports-world-gain-grupo-mexico-drops.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index (MEXBOL)  fell 0.1 percent to 36,785.34.  Grupo Aeromexico SAB (AEROMEX*)  (AEROMEX* MM), Mexico’s largest
airline by passengers, rose for the ninth time in 10 days,
advancing 3.5 percent to 24.49 pesos. Oil declined for a third
day as German industrial output weakened, signaling cheaper fuel
costs that may spur  air travel .  Grupo Sports World SAB (SPORTS)  , a Mexican gym operator,
climbed 2.9 percent to 12.98 pesos. Revenue will increase 50
percent in 2012 from the previous year because of new openings
and a projected pickup in memberships, the company said in a
filing.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, gained 1.5 percent to 616.38 pesos. Silver
futures for March delivery rose as much as 1.8 percent to $29.21
an ounce on the Comex.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
